i ordered using a delivery app and part of my order was missing; when i called, the man who picked up was not only helpful but kind. he comped my missing items and also offered me a drink on the house if i were to come by. i so appreciate the kindness i received during such a difficult time, and will definitely be returning. the food is also excellent, reminiscent of in n out but with a better bun! highly recommend.

Wanted to try this place and ordered the hot chicken sandwich with fries. Everything was perfect the sandwich had alot of love and inspiration inside that you can taste. Will definitely be a regular spot for me.

Was excited to try this place given their selection of vegetarian options. The vegetarian fried chicken was amazing. What wasn’t so amazing was the service. I came on a Sunday around 5 pm and the place was largely empty. I placed my order and then my boyfriend placed his. His burger came in a reasonable time. Mine didn’t. We waited around for about 25 minutes, watching the cashier read a book and the cook on her phone. Still no sandwich. My boyfriend finally inquired about my order and we were told the printer had been having issues and didn’t print my ticket. Woman seemed apologetic but then we waited another 10 minutes — during which I saw the cook again on her phone—and all she offered was a lame “sorry” and extra sauces. Overall it just put a bad taste in my mouth and overshadowed the good sandwich.

The flavor is strange... but good.  I was really impressed with the corn dog in particular.  If you feel like that you have become a one-trick pony. A one-stop shop of always getting your go-to fast food items, maybe it is time to spice up your life and introduce some real strangggeeee. Get some strange flavors. Rise above your preconceived notions.  I know, I know. You want that bacon cheese burger with ranch - I feel ya. I know you´re only human, but then strange flavors is eactly the type of food that ignite some of that passion back into you.

Most importantly, the burger is mind-blowingly good.  Second of all, the people who work here provided me with incredible customer service and went above and beyond to complete my order after some unusual circumstances. When I ordered on Seamless, my order was apparently stolen by somebody posing as a delivery person. They called me right away to apologize and let me know they would send me another order. They explained this has become a regular occurrence in recent times (sad!). The owner personally drove my meal to me to ensure it wasn’t stolen again and apologized profusely, which he honestly didn’t need to do! These guys are so great and clearly working hard in these tough times! Let’s keep supporting them everybody!

This is probably my third or fourth time ordering from Strange Flavor during quarantine and it's always great. Their fried chicken sandwich is awesome and I got the animal fries for the first time and they're always great. Thanks!!

I made an order through UberEats and was so disappointed​. After instructing that the patties on my burger be prepared well done they burger was medium rare.  To be fair to them the wild fries were very good. Disappointed in the burger tho.
Delicious burger shack inside of the Johnson's. Though it doesn't advertise it, all of the burgers can be prepared with veggie patties. The long bean tempura is delicious!

Both kinds of burgers were excellent, but if I had to pick one, it would be the Pops. Animal style fries were awesome, too. Really interesting atmosphere -- something you only find in Brooklyn. Walking through the front doors, Strange is on the right, then there's an open space with a bed, couches, picnic table, and seats all on that fake grass carpet stuff, and a storefront-style window/door setup for The Johnson's bar. It's cool and the system works well: walk in, order your food go back and grab a beer, get your food, and chow down on both, where ever you like.
Move over, Five Guys! These are officially the best fries I've ever tasted.  Not to mention the smokey ketchup, I want a huge bottle of it to bring with me everywhere.

amazing, honest, thoughtful food coming from two REALLY hard working dudes. go out of your way for the chicken wings, they were unbelievably good. you will discern such vivid flavors that you will be contemplating the meal for days/planning your return trip. thank you strange flavor!!!
